properties.NAME: Smithsonian National Museum of Natural History
properties.ADDRESS: 10th St. & Constitution Ave. NW, Washington, DC 20560
properties.DESCRIPTION: The world's most visited natural history museum featuring dinosaur exhibits, gems, and cultural artifacts.

properties.NAME: National Museum of African American History and Culture
properties.DESCRIPTION: The only national museum devoted exclusively to African American history and culture.

properties.NAME: National Museum of American History
properties.DESCRIPTION: Explores American history through exhibitions on science, technology, culture, and the arts.

properties.NAME: National Museum of the American Indian
properties.ADDRESS: 4th St. & Independence Ave. SW, Washington, DC 20560
properties.DESCRIPTION: Dedicated to the life, languages, literature, history, and arts of Native Americans.

properties.NAME: Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Houses the largest collection of historic aircraft and spacecraft in the world.

properties.NAME: The Phillips Collection
properties.DESCRIPTION: America's first museum of modern art featuring Impressionist and American modern art.

properties.NAME: National Museum of Women in the Arts
properties.ADDRESS: 1250 New York Ave. NW, Washington, DC 20005
properties.DESCRIPTION: The only major museum in the world solely dedicated to celebrating women's achievements in the visual arts.

properties.NAME: National Portrait Gallery
properties.ADDRESS: 8th St. & G Pl. NW, Washington, DC 20001
properties.DESCRIPTION: Features portraits of notable Americans who have shaped U.S. history and culture.

properties.NAME: National Geographic Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Explores the world through exhibitions on science, exploration, and culture.

properties.NAME: Baltimore Museum of Art
properties.DESCRIPTION: One of the largest art museums in the United States with a collection spanning from ancient mosaics to contemporary art.

properties.NAME: Walters Art Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Features art from ancient Egypt to 19th-century Europe, including medieval armor and Renaissance paintings.

properties.NAME: American Visionary Art Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Dedicated to self-taught artists and visionary art, featuring unique and unconventional works.

properties.NAME: National Aquarium
properties.DESCRIPTION: One of the nation's premier aquariums featuring thousands of marine animals and exhibits.

properties.NAME: Glenstone Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: A private contemporary art museum set on 230 acres of rolling hills and unspoiled woodland.

properties.NAME: Strathmore
properties.DESCRIPTION: A multi-disciplinary arts center featuring concerts, exhibitions, and educational programs.

properties.NAME: National Museum of the Marine Corps
properties.DESCRIPTION: Honors the commitment, accomplishments, and sacrifices of Marines throughout history.

properties.NAME: National Museum of African Art
properties.DESCRIPTION: The only national museum in the United States dedicated to the collection, exhibition, and study of African art.

properties.NAME: Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden
properties.ADDRESS: Independence Ave. SW & 7th St. SW, Washington, DC 20560
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Smithsonian's museum of international modern and contemporary art, featuring a world-class sculpture garden.

properties.NAME: International Spy Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: The world's premier collection of international espionage artifacts on public display.

properties.NAME: National Building Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: America's premier cultural institution dedicated to the history and impact of the built environment.

properties.NAME: Hillwood Estate, Museum & Gardens
properties.DESCRIPTION: Former home of Marjorie Merriweather Post, featuring Russian imperial art and French decorative arts.

properties.NAME: Renwick Gallery
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Smithsonian's museum of American craft and decorative arts, featuring contemporary works.

properties.NAME: Textile Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Part of the George Washington University, featuring textiles and carpets from around the world.

properties.NAME: National Museum of American Jewish Military History
properties.DESCRIPTION: Documents and preserves the contributions of Jewish Americans to the peace and freedom of the United States.

properties.NAME: Kreeger Museum
properties.DESCRIPTION: A private art museum featuring 19th and 20th century paintings, sculptures, and African art.

properties.NAME: Ford's Theatre
properties.DESCRIPTION: Historic theater where President Abraham Lincoln was assassinated, now a working theater and museum.

properties.NAME: United States Holocaust Memorial Museum
properties.ADDRESS: 100 Raoul Wallenberg Pl. SW, Washington, DC 20024

properties.NAME: Newseum
properties.DESCRIPTION: Interactive museum of news and journalism, now closed but historically significant.

properties.NAME: Arlington National Cemetery
properties.DESCRIPTION: A military cemetery honoring those who have served the United States, including the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.

properties.NAME: Mount Vernon
properties.ADDRESS: 3200 Mount Vernon Memorial Hwy, Mount Vernon, VA 22121

properties.NAME: Torpedo Factory Art Center
properties.DESCRIPTION: Former torpedo factory now housing the largest collection of working artists' studios in the U.S.

properties.NAME: Carlyle House Historic Park
properties.DESCRIPTION: 18th-century Georgian mansion where General Braddock planned the French and Indian War campaign.

properties.NAME: George Washington's Distillery & Gristmill
properties.ADDRESS: 5514 Mount Vernon Memorial Hwy, Alexandria, VA 22309
properties.DESCRIPTION: Reconstructed 18th-century distillery and gristmill, part of the Mount Vernon estate.
